{
  "texts": [
    "This dual approach enhances the network's feature extraction capability.The neck module consists of ELAN-L, Upsample, MP2 and SPPCSPC modules using the PAFPN Path Aggregation Feature Pyramid Network (PAFPN) architecture.",
    "The neck part combines the feature maps obtained from the different layers of the backbone module and sends them as input to the head module.",
    "The SPPCSPC module consists of CBS modules and MaxPool layers with different sizes of parallel max pooling (Fig. 5).",
    "The ELAN-L module has a similar structure to the ELAN module, but it combines five different outputs (Fig. 5).",
    "The Up-sample module consists of the CBS module and is used for upsampling."
  ]
}